Students acquire pieces from both the obligatory repertoire and according to free choice (lecturer and students). In the course of co-operation students' attention is drawn to problematic areas as well as individual characteristics (technical skills, improvisational vocabulary). Different positions in an ensemble (the role of a leader and a role of a professional group member) are given to participating students to gain the widest possible variety of personal experience.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims at developing independent group leading skills, skills to prepare repertoire for a concert and/or studio work. Application of specialized skills among colleagues. Usage of existing possibilities (characteristic features of different ensemble settings).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student knows the principles of ensemble instruction, can perform repertoire in a variety of styles, forms and groups, conduct their arrangement, cooperate with their ensemble members and perform both as a soloist and accompanist.
